(1) 2866 West 6th Street, west side, between Neptune Ave., and Sheepshead Bay Road, showing The Harvest, formerly the Coney Island House, later the Oceanic Hotel. It formerly stood, prior to 1921, at No. 622 Neptune Ave.

December 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, also showing overhead the Culver (B.M.T) Line.

December 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) The same, another view. Once a railroad ran from this Hotel to the beach and the Cars left every few minutes to accommodate the guests.

December 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(4) The same, in an abandoned state.

October 1928.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
